11 C. Upon the filing of a protest to the petition, the Supreme
12 Court shall then fix a day, not less than ten (10) business days
13 thereafter, at which time it will hear testimony and arguments for
14 and against the sufficiency of such petition.
15 D. A protest filed by anyone hereunder may, if abandoned by the
16 party filing same, be revived within five (5) business days by any
17 other citizen. After such hearing the Supreme Court shall decide
18 whether such petition is in the form required by the statutes. If
19 the Court is at the time adjourned, the Chief Justice shall
20 immediately convene the same for such hearing. No objection to the
21 sufficiency shall be considered unless it has been made and filed as
22 herein provided.
